# @param {Integer[]} max_heights
# @return {Integer}
def maximum_sum_of_heights(max_heights)
  n = max_heights.length
  max_sum = 0
  
  # Iterate through each element to consider it as the peak of the mountain
  (0...n).each do |peak|
    sum = max_heights[peak]
    min_left = max_heights[peak]
    min_right = max_heights[peak]

    # Expand to the left from the peak, ensuring we don't exceed the max heights
    (peak - 1).downto(0) do |i|
      min_left = [min_left, max_heights[i]].min
      sum += min_left
    end

    # Expand to the right from the peak, ensuring we don't exceed the max heights
    (peak + 1...n).each do |i|
      min_right = [min_right, max_heights[i]].min
      sum += min_right
    end

    # Update the maximum sum if this configuration is higher
    max_sum = [max_sum, sum].max
  end
  
  max_sum
end
